This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with network overlays and inter-domain paths. It could also belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it involves strategically selecting relays in Colocation Facilities. The paper also touches upon the topic of security (cs.CR) as it discusses the potential gains of using relays in Colos. Additionally, it could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it deals with real-time applications and network optimization. Finally, it could belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-category as it involves analyzing the performance of different types of relays.
